[
    {
        "content": "<p>For this program</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Rust\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">main</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>: <span class=\"kt\">u64</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"p\">)}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>the compiler will insert a load though <code>y</code> before returning:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"GAS\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nl\">example:</span><span class=\"err\">:</span><span class=\"nl\">main:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">pushq</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nv\">%rax</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">movq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">$5</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">%rsp</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">movq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">%rsp</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">%rdi</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">callq</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"p\">*</span><span class=\"no\">foo@GOTPCREL</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">%rip</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">movq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">%rsp</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">%rax</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">popq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">%rcx</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">retq</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But <code>y</code> is an immutable reference and it is live across the call to <code>foo()</code>. So the compiler should be able to assume that it did not change, and there is no <code>UnsafeCell</code> involved. </p>\n<p>Does anyone know where this behavior is documented? I can't find it anywhere.</p>",
        "id": 416584551,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1705588721
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It should just const propagate and return 5</p>",
        "id": 416584699,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1705588770
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Although the optimization you mention is valid, it's not guaranteed.</p>",
        "id": 416584865,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1705588806
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So my understanding that it is allowed to do so is correct?</p>",
        "id": 416584994,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1705588844
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes.</p>",
        "id": 416585086,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1705588873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was able to write a program that shows the behaviour:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kt\">u64</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"o\">+*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"GAS\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nl\">example:</span><span class=\"err\">:</span><span class=\"nl\">bar:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">pushq</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nv\">%rbx</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">movq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">%rdi</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">%rbx</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">callq</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"p\">*</span><span class=\"no\">foo@GOTPCREL</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">%rip</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">leaq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">%rax</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">%rbx</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">%rax</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">popq</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">%rbx</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">retq</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The instruction <code> leaq    (%rax,%rbx,2), %rax</code> adds 2x <code>*x</code> as it was loaded before the call to the return value of the call.</p>",
        "id": 416635115,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1705605739
